title.rendered: Sydney vs Brisbane, Australian T20 League, Eliminator, 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Sydney: Matthew Gilkes (wk), David Warner, Jason Sangha, Oliver Davies, Alex Ross, Daniel Sams, Ben Cutting, Nathan McAndrew, Chris Green (c), Gurinder Sandhu, Usman Qadir

Brisbane: Josh Brown, Usman Khawaja (c), Marnus Labuschagne, Matt Renshaw, Sam Hain, Jimmy Peirson (wk), Michael Neser, James Bazley, Spencer Johnson, Mitchell Swepson, Matthew Kuhnemann

Venue: Sydney Showground, Sydney

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 122

2nd innings average score: 183

Wickets per innings: 5

Type: Gets better for batting in the second innings

Wins

Batting 1st: —

Batting 2nd: 100%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

These teams have already met twice in this tournament. Matthew Gilkes (59 off 36 and 2 catches) and James Bazley (4 for 22 and 29 off 24) were the power players in the first and second game respectively.

Daniel Sams has enjoyed playing against Brisbane. Besides bagging 16 wickets in 11 games, he averages 28 with the bat including the highest score of 65*

Unfortunately for Matt Renshaw, his previous two innings against Sydney in this edition ended with scores of 9 and 0.

It has not been a successful time for David Warner this season. After 5 innings, he averages only 12.

6 fifties have been registered in the last 3 games at the venue, out of which 5 have come during chasing.

In the same period, a spinner hasn’t taken more than 3 wickets per innings at the Sydney Showground. Both three-fors have gone the way of the seamers.

Only 14 sixes have been hit at the venue in the last 3 games.
